description: Quill gets mixed up in a game of deceit when Gamora tries to pit her siblings, Nebula and Korath, against each other.
name: The Backstabbers

description: Lisa befriends Harper, a new kid at school who happens to be super-rich. Then, Homer befriends Harper's dad and is able to enjoy the perks of Lisa having a rich friend, as well. But Lisa decides that Harper is a bully and moves to end the friendship, which prompts Homer to try and smooth things over so he can continue to enjoy the good life.
name: Friend with Benefit

description: Peter gets a check in the mail from the sale of his mother's home and he remembers that all of his old porn is still in there. When he returns to retrieve his stash, he finds a 'to Peter from Peter' tape and realizes that his life has amounted to nothing. Reeling from his own failures, Peter then attempts to fix Chris before it's too late, and forces his son to spend time with Brian.
name: Peter, Chris, & Brian

description: After recent events, Barry (Grant Gustin) decides it's time to confront Zoom and comes up with a dangerous plan. Caitlin (Danielle Panabaker) sides with Jay (guest star Teddy Sears) and deems it too dangerous for Barry to engage with the speed demon. However, Iris (Candice Patton) shows her support and brings forth a surprising ally. We see what Earth-2 Harrison Wells' (Tom Cavanagh) life was like before coming through the breech.
name: Enter Zoom

description: Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) is frantic when she learns that Ray (guest-star Brandon Routh) is alive and being held by Damien Darhk (guest-star Neal McDonough). Felicity's guilt over not finding Ray sooner causes tension between her and Oliver (Stephen Amell). Meanwhile, Sara (guest-star Caity Lotz) joins Laurel (Katie Cassidy), Thea (Willa Holland) and the team on a rescue mission for Ray. However, the effects of the Lazarus Pit take over and threaten to jeopardize the entire operation. Donna Smoak (guest star Charlotte Ross) returns to Star City.
name: Lost Souls

description:
When the rebels need a new ship to help break an Imperial blockade of a struggling planet, Hera is dispatched on a dangerous mission to meet with an eccentric ship engineer. Hera earns his trust and completes a successful test flight in the harsh conditions of the planet's atmosphere.

Hera's amazing piloting skills will be showcased as she embarks on a dangerous mission to acquire a new ship, the B-Wing, to turn the tide in a crucial battle against the Empire.
name: Wings of the Master

deck: In an attempt to finally defeat the Turtles once and for all, the Shredder assembles Leatherhead, Tempestra, Scumbug, Chrome Dome, Antrax, The Rat King and Slash to form a team that proves too much for the turtles.
description: When the turtles are caught by Shredder's Rogues and left to die with a ticking time bomb, Splinter has April contact Casey Jones and Zach to rescue them.
name: Night of the Rogues

description: When Casey Jones discovers a hypercube, he accidentally unleashes a fourth dimensional being called Wyrm.
name: The Weird World of Wyrm

description: Kermit goes to Miss Piggy for help getting Denise a birthday gift, meanwhile Kristin Chenoweth threatens the Electric Mayhem friendship.
name: The Ex-Factor

first_appearance_teams.name: Doctor Teeth and the Electric Mayhem

team_credits.name: Doctor Teeth and the Electric Mayhem

description: Proper Japanese Title: オラも来たぞ！ビルス星で修行開始だ！(Ora mo Kita zo! Birusu-sei de Shugyō Kaishi da!)
name: I’ve Come Too! Training Begins on Beerus’ Planet!

description: The S.H.I.E.L.D. team discovers dangerous truths about the ATCU, and Ward's plans to destroy S.H.I.E.L.D. take a surprising twist.
name: Many Heads, One Tale

has_staff_review.name: Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. Episode #308 - "Many Heads, One Tale"

description: Knuckles tries to make amends for a past misdeed, but he only succeeds at making things worse.
name: Counter Productive

series.name: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic

deck: Ash returns to the book store that once helped him translate the Necronomicon.
description: A mysterious woman finds the destruction at Kelly's parents' farm. Meanwhile, Ash, Pablo and Kelly continue their quest with the Necronomicon and Fisher finds herself in another terrifying, inexplicable situation.
name: Books From Beyond

has_staff_review.name: Ash vs Evil Dead Episode #103 - “Books From Beyond”

description: When Groot is infected by a super-evolved Venom Symbiote, Rocket must go to extreme measures to save his leafy friend.
name: Hitchin' a Ride

description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.
name: Just Friends

description: Kara's Thanksgiving may be ruined when she suspects her foster mother, Dr. Danvers (Helen Slater), who is coming to town, disapproves of her new role as a superhero. Also, when an accident transforms a volatile CatCo employee into the villainous Livewire, she targets Cat and Supergirl.
name: Livewire

description: Mordecai and Rigby have to take Benson's new pet pig back to his apartment.
name: Benson's Pig

description: Grodd returns to Central City and kidnaps Caitlin (Danielle Panabaker). Barry (Grant Gustin) and team race to find her before it's too late. Meanwhile, Cisco (Carlos Valdes) plans his first date with the new barista at Jitters, Kendra Saunders (guest star Ciara Renee) and Patty (guest star Shantel VanSanten) begins to suspect Barry is hiding something from her.
name: Gorilla Warfare

description: Team Green Arrow's ongoing battle with Damien Darhk (Neal McDonough) is complicated by a shocking revelation. Thea's (Willa Holland) bloodlust returns and she loses control in front of Alex (guest-star Parker Young).
name: Brotherhood

description: Gordon confronts a suspect who is connected to Galavan, but falls short of obtaining any information. Meanwhile, Bruce gets one step closer to discovering the name of his parents' killer.
name: The Son of Gotham

description: In order to get high school credits, Rigby has to pass a foreign language class taught by Benson in China.
name: Hello China

description: Sabine is assigned a mission to escort a courier of secret information vital to the rebel cause to a rendezvous point. The task is quickly complicated by the arrival of Sabine's old friend and partner, Ketsu, who is looking to collect the bounty on the courier. Learn more about Sabine's mysterious backstory when bounty hunter Ketsu is introduced.
name: Blood Sisters

description: After the other Titans are injured, Beast Boy donates his blood to save them.
name: Animals, It's Just A Word!

description: It's Beast Boy's birthday! Will the other Titans remember?
name: BBBDay!

description: Starfire is visited by three ghosts and shown the true meaning of Black Friday.
name: Black Friday

description: Personal and professional stress get the better of Kara when she goes too far during a training exercise against Red Tornado, a military cyborg commissioned by Lucy Lane's father, General Sam Lane. Also, Cat's tough exterior is shaken by a visit from her judgmental mother, Katherine, and Alex enlists Winn to look into her father's mysterious death.
name: Red Faced

description: As HRG tries to help Tommy prepare to save the world, Carlos infiltrates Sunstone Manor and Taylor Kravid connects with Hero Truther. Greg Grunberg guest stars.
name: Sundae, Bloody Sundae

description: The destinies of Noah (Jack Coleman) and Luke (Zachary Levi) finally intersect as Malina unleashes her true power to save those around her. Tommy (Robbie Kay) may need to join forces with his enemy, Erica Kravid (Rya Khilstedt), to complete his mission. Meanwhile, Carlos confronts his violent past while under the watchful eyes of Matt Parkman (guest star Greg Grunberg). Elsewhere, Ren (guest star Toru Uchikado) is tasked with the impossible mission of finding Miko (Kiki Sukezane).
name: 11:53 to Odessa

description: Tenzin tasks Jinora, Ikki, and Meelo with a mission of the utmost importance - to find Korra.
name: The Calling

description: Kuvira threatens Zaofu; Bolin is caught in the middle of the bad blood between Su Beifong and Kuvira.
name: Enemy at the Gates

description: Korra returns to her role as the Avatar, but is she really ready for action? Bolin and Varrick break from Kuvira's army.
name: The Battle of Zaofu

description: Korra returns to Republic City and Team Avatar faces their first mission together in three years when Prince Wu goes missing; Bolin and Varrick are on the lam.
name: Reunion

description: A look back at Team Avatar's journey; Varrick tells the story of the greatest move ever made.
name: Remembrances

description: The spirit vines in Republic City start abducting people and it's up to Korra to figure out why.
name: Beyond the Wilds

description: Bolin helps Opal and Lin save the Beifongs from Kuvira; Korra visits the Spirit World looking for help.
name: Operation Beifong

description: Korra and Team Avatar try to stop Kuvira from moving against Republic City; Kuvira unveils a deadly new weapon.
name: Kuvira's Gambit

description: Team Avatar clashes with Kuvira on the streets of Republic City; Pema and Prince Wu help evacuate innocent citizens.
name: Day of the Colossus

description: The fate of the Earth Kingdom and the Avatar's life is at stake, when Korra comes face to face with Kuvira.
name: The Last Stand

description:
Proper Japanese Title: バルバトス

The adults of CGS flee in the face of Gjallarhorn's attack, using Mikazuki and the other children as decoys. Gathering the children who have been left behind, Orga decides to fight back against Gjallarhorn, and puts a certain plan into motion.
name: Barbatos

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 散華 (Sange)

Thanks to Mikazuki and the Gundam Barbatos, Orga's group has temporarily repulsed Gjallarhorn, though not without many sacrifices. As they are discussing their next move, one of Gjallarhorn's Graze mobile suits again appears at the CGS base.
name: Glorious Demise

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 命の値段 (Inochi no Nedan)

Kudelia is distressed that so many boys have lost their lives because of her. Mikazuki takes her to the farm run by Biscuit's grandmother, where an unexpected encounter awaits.
name: The Price of Life

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 赤い空の向こう (Akai Sora no Mukō)

Kudelia and Tekkadan finally leave Mars behind them and head for Earth. With a ship waiting for them, they attempt to travel by shuttle to a low-orbital station, but are attacked by Coral's Gjallarhorn forces.
name: Beyond the Red Sky

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 彼等について (Karera ni Tsuite)

The members of Tekkadan need a guide in order to reach Earth despite Gjallarhorn's surveillance. To gain a powerful backer, they attempt to negotiate with Teiwaz, which is based in the Jupiter Sphere.
name: As For Them

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 拉致 (Rachi)

Abruptly abducted in the dead of night, a loan shark offers Hazama and other captives the option of wiping their debt clean, at a cost--they must offer their heart to a certain man of means. However, the black market doctor goes AWOL and the heart transplant is no go...
name: Abduction

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 脱走兵 (Dassouhei)

Having witnessed Hazama's skills first-hand, Okamato visits his apartment bent on uncovering his secret. All she finds are evidence of Hazama's stringent surgical practice regimen using fish, pig feet and the like as subjects. Suddenly, they hear a groan next door...
name: Deserters

description:
Proper Japanese Title: そのためのハッカドールです (Sonotame no Hackadooru desu)

A company's fate lies in the hands of a huge project. However, with insufficient funding and an increase in bugs, this new operating system's launch date seems hopeless. If this project fails, the company tanks. Then, the Hackadolls are inputted into the system...
name: That's What HackaDolls Are For

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 先にシャワー浴びてきなよ (Saki ni Shawaa Abitekinayo)

#2 takes on the advancement of a client suffering from the big V. She ends up feeling something similar to excitement over this desperate, yet pure virgin. With a sunset and a moody atmosphere, the couple's feelings advance to the next level…
name: Take A Shower First

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 4号はダテじゃない！ (4gou wa Date janai!)

Unlike the one-dimensional, non-progressing Hackadolls, Hackadoll #4 is finally rolled out. Now overly specific #4 begins to bolster up the ditzy Hackadolls?!
name: #4 Isn't Just for Show!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 思い出のナーニー (Omoide no Naanii)

There's an outbreak of some serious bugs in cyberspace, sending the Hackadolls into a tizzy. Their hands, feet, and entire bodies are damaged until they lose something very important. Meanwhile, they receive their summoning call. The comparatively sane #3 heads out to advance the client...
name: A Thing of the Past

description: The Hackadolls get mixed up with a hard-as-nails production assistant and wind up advancing an anime. But, when faced with the gap between fantasy and reality, the girls are crushed. They shall continue to work like dogs until KUROBAKO's White Box is complete.
name: KUROBAKO

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ハコネちゃんと秘密箱 (Hakone-chan to Himitsu-bako)

Haruna's sister, Aki, doesn't believe is the spirit of the hot springs, but while they're taking a bath, she shows them her powers.
name: Hakone-chan and the Secret Box

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ハコネちゃんとハコネコ (Hakone-chan to Hakoneko)

Hakone-chan shows off her talents and lands a job.
name: Hakone-chan and Hakoneko

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ハコネちゃんと観光大使 (Hakone-chan to Kankō Taishi)

Hakone, the new tour ambassador for Yumoto, works a little too hard.
name: Hot Spring Spirit Hakone-chan

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ハコネちゃんとハコネ様 (Hakone-chan to Hakone-sama)

Hakone gets a level up!
name: Hakone-chan and Hakone-sama

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ハコネちゃんとミヤちゃん (Hakone-chan to Miya-chan)

A new hotel opens up next to Shunjusou. The owner is a girl named Miki, another hot spring spirit.
name: Hakone-chan and Miya-chan

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 小森さんは力持ち！ (Komori-san wa Chikaramochi!)

The girls think that Komori-san acts a little bit too much like a guy, but they realize quickly their assumptions may have been incorrect...
name: Komori-san is strong!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 小森さんは人気者！ (Komori-san wa ninki-sha!)

Shuri can't decline the absurd requests Megumi and Masako throw at her. Looking at how everyone in class relies on Shuri, Megumi comes to a realization and...
name: Komori-san is popular!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 小森さんは何でも屋？ (Komori-san wa nandemoya?)

The athletic Shuri gets asked to participate in the volleyball team's match, but she finds it hard to make plays. Megumi gets worried about her and...
name: Komori-san Can Do Anything?

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 根岸さんはソツがない！ (Negishi-san wa sotsu ga nai!)

Megumi gets the feeling that Shuri declines her often, and Masako, who insists she won't be declined, seems to be relied upon frequently as the class rep.
name: Negishi-san Has It All Covered!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 大谷くんは頼られたい！ (Ōtani-kun wa tayora retai!)

Classmate Otani-kun insists he'll never depend on Shuri, but Shuri accepts that as well.
name: Otani-kun Wants to Be Asked for Help!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 消えた自転車は知っている　その2 (Kieta Jitensha wa Shitteiru Sono 2)

Aya and the gang investigate the disappearance of Wakatake's bike.
name: The Missing Bike Knows Part 2

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 消えた自転車は知っている その3 (Kieta Jitensha wa Shitteiru Sono 3)

Aya and the gang find Wakatake's bicycle wrecked.
name: The Missing Bike Knows Part 3

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 消えた自転車は知っている　その4 (Kieta Jitensha wa Shitteiru Sono 4)

The group figures out who stole the bike, but Aya isn't convinced they should take matters into their own hands.
name: The Missing Bike Knows Part 4

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 卵ハンバーグは知っている その1 (Tamago Hamburger wa Shitte Iru Sono 1)

The team makes it to middle school. Aya's mom tells her not to hang out with the new guy who sits next to him in class.
name: The Egg Hamburg Steak Knows Part 1

description: Proper Japanese Title: 卵ハンバーグは知っている その2 (Tamago Hamburger wa Shitte Iru Sono 2)
name: The Egg Hamburg Steak Knows Part 2

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 始まってるよ！第一回新キャラオーディション！ (Hajimatteru yo! Daiichikai Shin Kyaraōdishon!)

There's an audition for this show.
name: Here We Go! New Character Auditions

description: A UFO touches down at the Nonomoto home.
name: Here We Go! An Alien Invader!

description: Matsushima becomes famous with her special dance.
name: Here We Go! Matsushima the Popular

description: The Nonomoto sisters go fishing at a lake with a tragic legend.
name: Here We Go! Dr. Wommy's Human Catastrophe Project

description: Why does the beautiful Konomi keep pestering Kukuru?
name: Here We Go! Kukuru and the Female Pakkun

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 華焔の魔女 (Kaen no majo)

Ayato Amagiri is a scholarship transfer student. What awaits him at the Seidoukan Academy?
name: Witch of the Resplendent Flames

description:
Proper Japanese Title: こちらコミック アース・スター編集部

Hana wants to run a monthly manga and nothing will stop her, not even lack of experience or knowledge.
name: This Is Comic Earth Star's Editorial Staff

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 毎日編集者

Hana’s unorthodox style of editing seems to fit well with the artist Shinobu.
name: Everyday Editor

description:
Proper Japanese Title: グラビア撮影日和

Hana is doing her best to make the magazine first gravure shoot the best, but it’s not going well.
name: Perfect Day for a Gravure Shoot

description:
Proper Japanese Title: あしすたんとの嬢（アシスタントガールズ）

The first issue of Earth Star is almost ready for the printer, but Shinobu’s manuscript is running late!
name: Assistant Girls

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 写植ミッドナイト

The girls learn that that the right font makes all the difference.
name: Phototypesetting Midnight

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 無限の校正

They may have gotten the manga to the printers but it is going to be a long night of proof reading.
name: Infinite Proofreading

description:
Proper Japanese Title: きみじか龍馬(リョーマ)ロード

With a small budget, the team sets out to do a 5 city research trip.
name: Impatient Ryouma Road

description:
Proper Japanese Title: コミスケの星

Team Earth Star attended their first Comisuke except for the Assistant Editor. She is the legendary…
name: Comisuke Planet

description:
Proper Japanese Title: あずかりもん

Working with a Mangaka can sometime leave the office feeling crowded.
name: Something Borrowed

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 骨愛ずる姫君 (Hone Mezuru Himegimi)

Tatewaki Shoutarou is an average high school student in Asahikawa City, Hokkaido Prefecture. However, hh has an unusual acquaintance by the name of Kujou Sakurako, who loves bones more than life itself. One day, on a bone gathering expedition along the shores of Mashike, they find a human skull...
name: The Princess Who Loves Bones

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 貴方のお家はどこですか (Anata no Ouchi wa Doko desu ka)

Shoutarou finds a little girl at a convenience store in the dead of night. Other than her nickname, Ii-chan, no one can figure out her real name and address. Finding a bloody handprint on her backpack, Shoutarou asks Sakurako for help. But their inquiries only lead them to a shocking realization...
name: Where Do You Live?

description:
Proper Japanese Title: テガミとテガミバチ (Tegami to Tegamibachi)

One day Lag Seeing finds himself shipped. His mother abducted by someone, he's now just a package sent by her to be delivered to a friend's house. Gauche Suede is a Letter Bee, a member of the Amberground national postal service, who is tasked with delivering this "letter," together with his partner Roda. The still young Lag rebels at Gauche's seemingly emotionless focus on his work, his heart still reeling from being torn from his mother, but as they head into a valley they are attacked by a ferocious creature known as a Gaichuu.
name: Letter and Letter Bee

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 異世界からの訪問者 (I Sekai Kara no Raihōsha)

Approximately four years ago, a gate to another world opened in Mikado City, and invaders called Neighbors appeared.
name: Visitor from the Other World

description: When Lord Dregg hires a bounty hunter to destroy the Ninja Turtles, the team flees to an abandoned space station!
name: The Outlaw Armaggon!

description: Shaggy and Scooby-Doo's favorite chef is finally opening his own restaurant, but a monstrous Yeti threatens the opening night. The gang has to solve the mystery before dessert is served, and Shaggy and Scooby have to resist eating all the food that's meant for the customers!
name: Kitchen Frightmare

description: Getting back to Alexandria proves hard.
name: Always Accountable

description: Kermit is worried when Fozzie decides to move in with his girlfriend and Scooter gets a crush on Chelsea Handler.
name: Too Hot to Handler

first_appearance_teams.name: Doctor Teeth and the Electric Mayhem

team_credits.name: Doctor Teeth and the Electric Mayhem

description: Jessica Jones is hired to find a pretty NYU student who's vanished, but it turns out to be more than a simple missing persons case.
name: AKA Ladies Night

description: Jessica vows to prove Hope's innocence, even though it means tracking down a terrifying figure from her own past.
name: AKA Crush Syndrome

description: It won't be easy to acquire or deploy. but Jessica thinks she's found a weapon to use against Kilgrave. Luke and Jessica bond over their similarities.
name: AKA It's Called Whiskey

description: A new case demands attention as Jessica tries to find out who's spying on her for Kilgrave. Trish's radio show yields unexpected consequences.
name: AKA 99 Friends

description: Despite Jessica's objections, Trish's new friend Simpson gets involved in the hunt for Kilgrave. Jessica recalls a pivotal moment in her life.
name: AKA The Sandwich Saved Me

description: Luke hires Jessica to help him find someone who may have skipped town, but she fears he'll learn too much about her history in the process.
name: AKA You're A Winner

description: Malcom, Simpson and Trish go rouge to prevent Jessica from carrying out an extreme plan to outwit Kilgrave.
name: AKA Top Shelf Perverts

description: Jessica experiences a strange homecoming courtesy of Kilgrave. Hograth's conflict with her estranged wife reaches a tipping point.
name: AKA WWJD?
